
[1]saffron

   SAF'FRON, n. [The radical sense is to fail, or to be hollow, or to be
   exhausted.

   1. A plant of the genus Crocus. The bastard saffron is of the genus
   Carthamus, and the meadow saffron of the genus Colchicum.

   2. In the materia medica, saffron is formed of the stigmata of the
   Crocus officinalis, dried on a kiln and pressed into cakes.

   SAF'FRON, a. Having the color of saffron flowers; yellow; as a saffron
                          face; a saffron streamer.

       SAF'FRON, v.t. To tinge with saffron; to make yellow; to gild.
